New Records: Victor Wembanyama scored his first career 50 points in a game.
Victor Wembanyama made the most 3-point attempts in a game in his career with 16 attempts.
Key Match Events: Victor Wembanyama scored 50 points in a 139-130 win over the Washington Wizards.
Wembanyama's performance included a mix of 3-pointers and drives, exploiting the Wizards' defense.
Pre-Game Insights: The matchup featured Wembanyama against his former Metropolitans 92 teammate Bilal Coulibaly and fellow Frenchman Alex Sarr.
Post-Match Reflections: Gregg Popovich, who has missed the past few games while recovering from a mild stroke, previously stated that he wants Wembanyama to shoot more 3s as part of the Spurs' long-term plan.
Wembanyama's performance was seen as a proof of concept for the Spurs' strategy of developing him as a perimeter player.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Wembanyama's three-game streak with at least six made 3-pointers.
Wembanyama's season-long 3-point percentage increased to 34 percent.
